Follow @coachnickod for more fitness and nutrition tips 💪

Staying injury-free and saving time is the new name of the game.

You probably have more responsibilities in your 30s than you did in your 20s, so you are probably more aware of how valuable your time can be.

One way to save time is to rely on HIIT instead of walking on a treadmill for half an hour ⏰

And men, fathers, business owners, leaders…

You can’t be out of commission with injuries to keep your households, companies and life goals on track.

A great way to remain healthy and injury-free is to try pause reps and tempo reps.

Lifting heavy is important but so is protecting your joints.

Longevity and sustainability is the name of the game for longterm results and peak performance.

Coach Nicko 👉 @coachnickod

node.text:
Male&Female BODY FAT %
🔥Follow @fitness_tipsters for more fitness tips
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So the main reason for this difference between mean and women is that at some point in their lives may nourish a fetus and then a baby from their own bodies, so women have to stock energy in the form of fat in anticipation of future pregnancies.  There's also the hormonal differences that play a role with men vs women as why they will carry more body fat.  For the most part women carry fat differently and in different areas of the body such as the buttocks, hips and navel midsection area. The scale can tell you how much total gross weight our body carries but it can't really tell you your bf%.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We weigh ourselves to find out how much "weight" we have lost, but do you really know how much "fat" you've lost. It's all very misleading right? The body is compromised of
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
lean muscle, fat tissue, organs, water, etc...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
You may have a healthy weight but not so healthy bf%. More than 30% for women and 20% body fat for men makes it more likely to be vulnerable to diseases that effects overweight and obese people. Too mcuh body fat is serious healthy risk.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Problems that may occur are:
-Hypertension
-Elevated blood lipids(cholesterol)
-Diabetes
-Mellitus
-Cardiovascular disease
-Respiratory dysfunction
-Gall bladder failure/disease⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
-Joint issues/disease
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
OK but lets flip the page on this and play devils advocate, being too thin can also cause issues. Now more than ever, people are worried about how much they weigh. In only the opposite direction people in a effort to lose weight and extra fat achieve being too lean only by popular misconceptions of what today's society deems fit.
Via @skiman.factual.fitness
.
.
